fuzz_extract_mem: assert `bit_count > 0` in dmc_unrar_bs_peek_uint32
(dmc_unrar.c:8592), called from dmc_unrar_huff_get_symbol via
dmc_unrar_bs_peek_bits with a zero-width Huffman table. The RAR5
decoder builds tables from archive-supplied code lengths; a malformed
archive can produce a table with table_size == 0, which then asks the
bitstream to peek 0 bits. 335-byte input, surfaced on the 60-second
post-fix smoke run of fuzz_extract_mem. Fixed by rejecting
uninitialized / zero-width Huffman decoders in
dmc_unrar_huff_get_symbol().
